[3] Cholera - Uganda (Yumbe)
Date: Wed, 16 Aug 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Daily Monitor [edited]
<http://www.monitor.co.ug/news/news081818.php>

A cholera outbreak in Yumbe district has claimed 3 and left 11 admitted in
the district main hospital.
The District Health Inspector, Mr Collins Angunda, on Wed, 16 Aug 2006,
said the epidemic was rampant in Apo, Kuru and Drajini sub-counties.
Angunda was speaking during an emergency meeting at the office of the chief
administrative officer.
He said 2 of the victims; a man and a 9-year-old girl were from Apo
subcounty while another woman died in Kuru subcounty. Angunda said 3 of
the patients were in a stable condition while the other 8 were doing badly.
Angunda said the district taskforce was investigating the outbreak of the
epidemic to find ways of combating it. He said their key case was a woman
who was suspected to have runaway from Oli Health Center in Arua, where she
had been earlier admitted on suspicion that she had contracted the disease.
The woman reportedly sneaked from the hospital and died at her home in
Jabala village.
[Byline: Kefa Atibun]
